This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for semantic role labeling and coreference resolution, which are common topics in the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also introduces a novel span-based labeling framework, which involves machine learning algorithms and could be relevant to the subfields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the applicability of the approach to the slot filling task, which could be relevant to the subfields of natural language processing (cs.NE) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
